From 46becccbb94cf6c565790c061261f71a2a3f0787 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: dirkwa <dirkwahrheit@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 21 Mar 2026 07:03:25 +1200
Subject: [PATCH] fix: resolve baconjs version mismatch between server and
 plugins

Plugins bundling BaconJS 0.7.x/1.x crash with "TypeError: e.isEnd is
not a function" when operating on the server's 3.x StreamBundle buses,
because 3.x Event objects use boolean properties while 1.x expects
methods.

Hook Module._resolveFilename so all require('baconjs') calls in the
process resolve to the server's 3.x copy, eliminating cross-version
Event object mismatches. Patch EventStream and Property prototypes to
restore the .map('.property') string shorthand from 1.x.
